13// This is the base class for object's body descriptors.
14//
15// Each BodyDescriptor subclass must provide the following methods:
16//
17// 1) Iterate object's body using stateful object visitor.
18//
19// template <typename ObjectVisitor>
20// static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, HeapObject obj, int
21// object_size,
22// ObjectVisitor* v);
23class BodyDescriptorBase {
24 public:
25 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
26 static inline void IteratePointers(Tagged<HeapObject> obj, int start_offset,
27 int end_offset, ObjectVisitor* v);
28
29 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
30 static inline void IteratePointer(Tagged<HeapObject> obj, int offset,
31 ObjectVisitor* v);
32
33 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
34 static inline void IterateCustomWeakPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
35 int start_offset, int end_offset,
36 ObjectVisitor* v);
37
38 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
39 static inline void IterateCustomWeakPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
40 int offset, ObjectVisitor* v);
41
42 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
43 static inline void IterateEphemeron(Tagged<HeapObject> obj, int index,
44 int key_offset, int value_offset,
45 ObjectVisitor* v);
46
47 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
48 static inline void IterateMaybeWeakPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
49 int start_offset, int end_offset,
50 ObjectVisitor* v);
51
52 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
53 static inline void IterateMaybeWeakPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> obj, int offset,
54 ObjectVisitor* v);
55
56 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
57 static inline void IterateTrustedPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> obj, int offset,
58 ObjectVisitor* visitor,
59 IndirectPointerMode mode,
60 IndirectPointerTag tag);
61 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
62 static inline void IterateCodePointer(Tagged<HeapObject> obj, int offset,
63 ObjectVisitor* visitor,
64 IndirectPointerMode mode);
65 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
66 static inline void IterateSelfIndirectPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
67 IndirectPointerTag tag,
68 ObjectVisitor* v);
69
70 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
71 static inline void IterateProtectedPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> obj, int offset,
72 ObjectVisitor* v);
73
74 protected:
75 // Returns true for all header and embedder fields.
76 static inline bool IsValidEmbedderJSObjectSlotImpl(Tagged<Map> map,
77 Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
78 int offset);
79
80 // Treats all header and embedder fields in the range as tagged.
81 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
82 static inline void IterateJSObjectBodyImpl(Tagged<Map> map,
83 Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
84 int start_offset, int end_offset,
85 ObjectVisitor* v);
86};
87
88// This class describes a body of an object without any pointers.
89class DataOnlyBodyDescriptor : public BodyDescriptorBase {
90 public:
91 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
92 static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
93 int object_size, ObjectVisitor* v) {}
94
95 private:
96 // Note: {SizeOf} is not implemented here; sub-classes will have to implement
97 // it.
98};
99
100// This class describes a body of an object in which all pointer fields are
101// located in the [start_offset, end_offset) interval.
102// All pointers have to be strong.
103template <int start_offset, int end_offset>
104class FixedRangeBodyDescriptor : public BodyDescriptorBase {
105 public:
106 static const int kStartOffset = start_offset;
107 static const int kEndOffset = end_offset;
108
109 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
110 static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
111 ObjectVisitor* v) {
112 IteratePointers(obj, start_offset, end_offset, v);
113 }
114
115 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
116 static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
117 int object_size, ObjectVisitor* v) {
118 IterateBody(map, obj, v);
119 }
120
121 // Note: {SizeOf} is not implemented here; sub-classes will have to implement
122 // it.
123};
124
125// This class describes a body of an object of a fixed size
126// in which all pointer fields are located in the [start_offset, end_offset)
127// interval.
128// All pointers have to be strong.
129template <int start_offset, int end_offset, int size>
130class FixedBodyDescriptor
131 : public std::conditional_t<
132 start_offset == end_offset, DataOnlyBodyDescriptor,
133 FixedRangeBodyDescriptor<start_offset, end_offset>> {
134 public:
135 static constexpr int kSize = size;
136
137 static inline int SizeOf(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
138 DCHECK_EQ(kSize, map->instance_size());
139 return kSize;
140 }
141};
142
143template <typename T>
144using FixedBodyDescriptorFor =
145 FixedBodyDescriptor<T::kStartOfStrongFieldsOffset,
146 T::kEndOfStrongFieldsOffset, T::kSize>;

148// This class describes a body of an object in which all pointer fields are
149// located in the [start_offset, object_size) interval.
150// All pointers have to be strong.
151template <int start_offset>
152class SuffixRangeBodyDescriptor : public BodyDescriptorBase {
153 public:
154 static const int kStartOffset = start_offset;
155
156 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
157 static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
158 int object_size, ObjectVisitor* v) {
159 IteratePointers(obj, start_offset, object_size, v);
160 }
161
162 // Note: {SizeOf} is not implemented here; sub-classes will have to implement
163 // it.
164};

166// This class describes a body of an object of a variable size
167// in which all pointer fields are located in the [start_offset, object_size)
168// interval.

170template <int start_offset>
171class FlexibleBodyDescriptor : public SuffixRangeBodyDescriptor<start_offset> {
172 public:
173 static inline int SizeOf(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> object);
174};

180// This class describes a body of an object in which all pointer fields are
181// located in the [start_offset, object_size) interval.
182// Pointers may be strong or may be Tagged<MaybeObject>-style weak pointers.
183template <int start_offset>
184class SuffixRangeWeakBodyDescriptor : public BodyDescriptorBase {
185 public:
186 static const int kStartOffset = start_offset;
187
188 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
189 static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
190 int object_size, ObjectVisitor* v) {
191 IterateMaybeWeakPointers(obj, start_offset, object_size, v);
192 }
193
194 // Note: {SizeOf} is not implemented here; sub-classes will have to implement
195 // it.
196};

198// This class describes a body of an object of a variable size
199// in which all pointer fields are located in the [start_offset, object_size)
200// interval.
201// Pointers may be strong or may be Tagged<MaybeObject>-style weak pointers.
202template <int start_offset>
203class FlexibleWeakBodyDescriptor
204 : public SuffixRangeWeakBodyDescriptor<start_offset> {
205 public:
206 static inline int SizeOf(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> object);
207};

209// This class describes a body of an object which has a parent class that also
210// has a body descriptor. This represents a union of the parent's body
211// descriptor, and a new descriptor for the child -- so, both parent and child's
212// slots are iterated. The parent must be fixed size, and its slots be disjoint
213// with the child's.
214template <class ParentBodyDescriptor, class ChildBodyDescriptor>
215class SubclassBodyDescriptor : public BodyDescriptorBase {
216 public:
217 // The parent must end be before the child's start offset, to make sure that
218 // their slots are disjoint.
219 static_assert(ParentBodyDescriptor::kSize <=
220 ChildBodyDescriptor::kStartOffset);
221
222 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
223 static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
224 ObjectVisitor* v) {
225 ParentBodyDescriptor::IterateBody(map, obj, v);
226 ChildBodyDescriptor::IterateBody(map, obj, v);
227 }
228
229 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
230 static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
231 int object_size, ObjectVisitor* v) {
232 ParentBodyDescriptor::IterateBody(map, obj, object_size, v);
233 ChildBodyDescriptor::IterateBody(map, obj, object_size, v);
234 }
235
236 static inline int SizeOf(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
237 // The child should know its full size.
238 return ChildBodyDescriptor::SizeOf(map, object);
239 }
240};
241
242// Visitor for exposed trusted objects with fixed layout according to
243// FixedBodyDescriptor.
244template <typename T, IndirectPointerTag kTag>
245class FixedExposedTrustedObjectBodyDescriptor
246 : public FixedBodyDescriptorFor<T> {
247 static_assert(std::is_base_of_v<ExposedTrustedObject, T>);
248 using Base = FixedBodyDescriptorFor<T>;
249
250 public:
251 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
252 static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
253 int object_size, ObjectVisitor* v) {
254 Base::IterateSelfIndirectPointer(obj, kTag, v);
255 Base::IterateBody(map, obj, object_size, v);
256 }
257};
258
259// A mix-in for visiting a trusted pointer field.
260template <size_t kFieldOffset, IndirectPointerTag kTag>
261struct WithStrongTrustedPointer {
262 template <typename Base>
263 class BodyDescriptor : public Base {
264 public:
265 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
266 static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
267 int object_size, ObjectVisitor* v) {
268 Base::IterateBody(map, obj, object_size, v);
269 Base::IterateTrustedPointer(obj, kFieldOffset, v,
270 IndirectPointerMode::kStrong, kTag);
271 }
272 };
273};
274
275template <size_t kFieldOffset>
276using WithStrongCodePointer =
277 WithStrongTrustedPointer<kFieldOffset, kCodeIndirectPointerTag>;
278
279// A mix-in for visiting an external pointer field.
280template <size_t kFieldOffset, ExternalPointerTag kTag>
281struct WithExternalPointer {
282 template <typename Base>
283 class BodyDescriptor : public Base {
284 public:
285 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
286 static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
287 int object_size, ObjectVisitor* v) {
288 Base::IterateBody(map, obj, object_size, v);
289 v->VisitExternalPointer(obj,
290 obj->RawExternalPointerField(kFieldOffset, kTag));
291 }
292 };
293};
294
295// A mix-in for visiting an external pointer field.
296template <size_t kFieldOffset>
297struct WithProtectedPointer {
298 template <typename Base>
299 class BodyDescriptor : public Base {
300 public:
301 template <typename ObjectVisitor>
302 static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, Tagged<HeapObject> obj,
303 int object_size, ObjectVisitor* v) {
304 Base::IterateBody(map, obj, object_size, v);
305 Base::IterateProtectedPointer(obj, kFieldOffset, v);
306 }
307 };
308};
309
310// Stack multiple body descriptors; the first template argument is the base,
311// followed by mix-ins.
312template <typename Base, typename FirstMixin, typename... MoreMixins>
313class StackedBodyDescriptor
314 : public StackedBodyDescriptor<
315 typename FirstMixin::template BodyDescriptor<Base>, MoreMixins...> {};
316
317// Define a specialization for the base case of only one mixin.
318template <typename Base, typename FirstMixin>
319class StackedBodyDescriptor<Base, FirstMixin>
320 : public FirstMixin::template BodyDescriptor<Base> {};
